  "justFinishedAt": "2026-03-09T22:58:46.879Z",
  "summary": "## Summary: New Page Setup Modal with AI Smart Rule Generation\n\n### Changes Implemented\n- When a new page is created from the sidebar, a modal dialog now appears asking the user to name the page and describe what it's about\n- The modal has a two-step flow:\n  1. **Describe step**: User enters a page name and describes the page's purpose in natural language\n  2. **Review step**: AI generates a clarified smart rule from the description, which the user can edit before saving\n- The generated smart rule is saved to the page with `smartActive: true`, enabling automatic content classification\n- Users can skip the modal at any step if they don't want to set up smart rules\n- The AI prompt instructs the classifier to generate a specific, actionable rule that avoids false positives while catching relevant content\n\n### Files Modified\n- `components/pages/PagesSidebar.tsx` — Added `NewPageSetupModal` import and state management; modal opens after page creation via `handleNewPage`\n\n### Files Created\n- `app/api/pages/generate-smart-rule/route.ts` — New API endpoint that takes a user's page description and uses OpenRouter AI to generate a clarified smart rule prompt\n- `components/pages/NewPageSetupModal.tsx` — Two-step modal component with page name input, description textarea, AI generation button, rule review/edit, and save/skip actions\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- The modal reuses the existing `Modal` component from `components/ui/Modal.tsx` for consistent accessibility (focus trap, escape key, backdrop)\n- The API endpoint follows existing patterns: `getRequiredUser()` for auth, `chatCompletion()` for AI, `TokenLimitError` handling\n- The `useUpdatePage` hook is used to save both the page title and generated smart rule in one mutation\n- Pre-existing type errors in `.next/types/validator.ts` (stale cache) and `app/api/pages/[pageId]/ask/route.ts` are unrelated to these changes\n- Sub-page creation via the tree item `+` button does not trigger the modal (only the sidebar \"New Page\" button does)"
}